hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: How much were you paid in your last job? bdmpharma.ma Aglianico is the fierce red grape of Campania. This captures some of its innate darkness; looming through the dense wine there’s a sense of old grey stone and antiquity. Remarkable to find such truthfulness in an everyday-priced wine. Like many Italian reds this has buoyant acidity – which is another way of saying it’s good with food. Think herby Tuscan sausages, hunter’s kebabs or tomato gnocchi.
